You cannot define `Number::print()` like that in the header file. It needs to be either marked inline, be in the class declaration itself, or in a separate cpp file.
```
class Number {
    public:
        virtual void print() const;
        virtual inline void print2() const;
        virtual void print3() const {} // OK
};

void Number::print() const {}  // not OK, linker error(s)
inline void Number::print2() const {}  // OK (the &quot;inline&quot; here is optional)
```

